            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nWhen discussing numbers in the previous text, we used cultures from Mesoamerica (*Abya Yala*) to examine the relationship between them (<htcite0>). However, we mentioned that, generally, in textbooks, numbers are presented in a way that differs from that of a sacred mountain. Before reaching a more abstract version, let us take an intermediate step. Observe the Shona kitchen (**Figure 1**) (<htcite1>).",
               "source": [
            {
               "type": 1,
               "uuid": "010490cd-6da9-4992-a765-8a03188da892",
               "text": "History Tracers Team",
               "page": "Reality",
               "date_time": {
                  "type": "gregory",
                  "year": "2026",
